513
00:29:55,135 --> 00:29:57,173
Yeah, that'shat they all say.

514
00:29:57,725 --> 00:29:59,133
"They"?

515
00:29:59,516 --> 00:30:02,800
How many... how many people
have you taught before me?

516
00:30:05,936 --> 00:30:09,022
Come on, mate,
I'll steal us a cab.

517
00:30:11,605 --> 00:30:13,981
You coming or not?

518
00:30:38,057 --> 00:30:41,300
Uh, so they suspended
me for six months.

519
00:30:43,096 --> 00:30:44,852
Oh, Matt.

520
00:30:45,317 --> 00:30:47,973
I actually thought this ability
was gonna be a good thing.

521
00:30:48,276 --> 00:30:50,192
And now I'm unemployed, and

522
00:30:50,488 --> 00:30:52,692
about to lose my marriage.

523
00:30:56,196 --> 00:30:58,070
You haven't lost that.

524
00:30:58,577 --> 00:31:01,860
- Not yet anyway.
- Thanks, that's encouraging.

525
00:31:03,825 --> 00:31:05,411
Look, we...

526
00:31:07,205 --> 00:31:09,913
We just have to
trust each other.

527
00:31:11,505 --> 00:31:13,333
I can do that.

528
00:31:20,515 --> 00:31:21,881
Now...

529
00:31:24,765 --> 00:31:27,760
So I'm gonna give
you one more freebie.

530
00:31:28,938 --> 00:31:31,180
What am I thinking?

531
00:31:36,407 --> 00:31:38,273
We're having a baby?

532
00:31:43,535 --> 00:31:46,031
We're having a baby!

533
00:31:54,377 --> 00:31:56,792
Nik, what have
they done to you?

534
00:31:58,806 --> 00:32:01,130
- If they catch you...
- They won't.

535
00:32:03,305 --> 00:32:04,931
Come closer.

536
00:32:05,135 --> 00:32:06,391
What is it?

537
00:32:07,475 --> 00:32:09,261
Your shirt.

538
00:32:10,775 --> 00:32:12,601
It smells like home.

539
00:32:14,815 --> 00:32:16,400
How's Micah?

540
00:32:18,405 --> 00:32:20,982
- Is he okay?
- He's fine.

541
00:32:23,156 --> 00:32:24,570
It's just...

542
00:32:26,246 --> 00:32:28,201
I can't do this, Nik.

543
00:32:28,418 --> 00:32:29,991
Not alone.

544
00:32:30,996 --> 00:32:32,251
I thought I could.

545
00:32:32,585 --> 00:32:34,383
I thought I could handle everything,
but I...

546
00:32:34,418 --> 00:32:36,251
D.L., you can't do this to me.

547
00:32:36,505 --> 00:32:38,751
I gotta find a way to
get you outta here.

548
00:32:39,466 --> 00:32:40,922
This is crazy.

549
00:32:41,177 --> 00:32:42,770
I can walk in here any
time I want, right?

550
00:32:42,805 --> 00:32:44,341
I should be able
to get you out.

551
00:32:44,635 --> 00:32:46,593
I am gonna be in here
for a long time.

552
00:32:46,805 --> 00:32:49,141
The rest of my life maybe.

553
00:32:49,558 --> 00:32:53,141
- You need to get used to that.
- Your son needs you.

554
00:32:53,185 --> 00:32:55,813
Damn it, D.L.,
that is not fair.

555
00:32:56,068 --> 00:32:59,153
I am counting on you.

556
00:32:59,525 --> 00:33:02,532
You know that I need
to stay in here.

557
00:33:02,657 --> 00:33:04,532
I need you, Nik.

558
00:33:05,656 --> 00:33:07,612
We need you.

559
00:33:09,288 --> 00:33:12,373
He's having such a
hard time without you.

560
00:33:12,878 --> 00:33:14,950
You need to talk to him.

561
00:33:16,588 --> 00:33:19,082
You need to be honest.

562
00:33:19,506 --> 00:33:23,510
He needs boundaries
and a strong hand.

563
00:33:26,975 --> 00:33:28,893
It's not too late.

564
00:33:34,726 --> 00:33:36,433
You need to go.

565
00:33:38,238 --> 00:33:39,602
Go.

566
00:34:35,305 --> 00:34:38,851
There's only 12 people in Kermit
with the last name "Gordon."

567
00:34:40,485 --> 00:34:42,890
So far, only three.

568
00:34:43,148 --> 00:34:45,941
None of them have ever
heard of Meredith.

569
00:34:47,447 --> 00:34:48,823
- Claire?
- Hold on.

570
00:34:50,196 --> 00:34:53,073
- I'll call you back.
- Claire?

571
00:34:54,038 --> 00:34:56,532
Sorry, I was just, uh,

572
00:34:56,786 --> 00:34:59,122
