about our report.

573
00:34:59,456 --> 00:35:04,623
Well, Molly in accounting is
married to a marine biologist,

574
00:35:04,838 --> 00:35:06,963
and he said that...

575
00:35:07,257 --> 00:35:09,250
You're already on top of it.

576
00:35:10,467 --> 00:35:14,683
Did you know that all three varieties of
manatee are vulnerable to extinction?

577
00:35:14,846 --> 00:35:16,552
No, I didn't.

578
00:35:23,026 --> 00:35:24,980
Is everything all right?

579
00:35:25,237 --> 00:35:27,113
We haven't talked in a while.

580
00:35:28,367 --> 00:35:30,320
Actually, there is something.

581
00:35:31,155 --> 00:35:32,442
Yeah?

582
00:35:35,247 --> 00:35:36,612
The bears.

583
00:35:37,128 --> 00:35:38,782
My stuffed bears.

584
00:35:39,626 --> 00:35:42,162
I think it's time
for them to migrate.

585
00:35:44,625 --> 00:35:48,170
I'm almost 16, Dad,
bears and talks can't last forever.

586
00:35:48,385 --> 00:35:52,801
Whether you're 16,
or 32, or 64...

587
00:35:52,845 --> 00:35:55,423
- When I'm 64, you'll...
- I will be there for you.

588
00:35:56,227 --> 00:35:59,183
Always.

589
00:36:02,647 --> 00:36:06,441
Don't you think it's time I learn
how to deal with my own problems?

590
00:36:17,246 --> 00:36:20,992
Well, dinner's in an hour.

591
00:36:21,248 --> 00:36:22,873
And, uh, do me a favor. No...

592
00:36:23,245 --> 00:36:25,663
No extinction talk
at the table.

593
00:36:25,717 --> 00:36:28,120
You know how sensitive
your mother is.

594
00:36:48,107 --> 00:36:49,771
You have a change of heart?

595
00:36:50,155 --> 00:36:51,441
My son.

596
00:36:55,235 --> 00:36:58,653
My family needs me. So...

597
00:36:58,995 --> 00:37:01,821
I want you to understand that
there are no guarantees.

598
00:37:01,875 --> 00:37:05,451
I don't care.
I need to get rid of Jessica.

599
00:37:06,378 --> 00:37:08,870
So you know what might help?

600
00:37:11,586 --> 00:37:16,210
If I could talk to her.
All right?

601
00:37:16,218 --> 00:37:18,670
- Isn't there another way?
- No.

602
00:37:18,936 --> 00:37:20,843
I'm afraid in cases like these,

603
00:37:20,976 --> 00:37:23,142
it is imperative that
I have interaction

604
00:37:23,145 --> 00:37:25,811
with all aspects of the
patient's personality.

605
00:37:26,108 --> 00:37:29,640
- Honey, let me talk to her.
- No!

606
00:37:30,818 --> 00:37:32,560
You can't.

607
00:37:33,446 --> 00:37:36,982
So let me put it to you this way.
Either I speak with Jessica,

608
00:37:36,988 --> 00:37:41,323
or you may not see your little
boy for a very, very long time.

609
00:37:54,348 --> 00:37:55,462
But...

610
00:37:56,306 --> 00:37:57,802
Wait.

611
00:38:07,936 --> 00:38:09,893
Micah, where have you been?

612
00:38:10,107 --> 00:38:11,600
I was worried to death.

613
00:38:11,607 --> 00:38:13,523
I was just out walking around.

614
00:38:14,155 --> 00:38:15,821
Sit down.

615
00:38:23,497 --> 00:38:26,331
Micah, we gotta
figure this out.

616
00:38:26,668 --> 00:38:29,080
'Cause the truth is your
mom's not coming home,

617
00:38:29,087 --> 00:38:31,752
and I'm having a
really hard time here.

618
00:38:32,216 --> 00:38:34,132
I can't get a job.

619
00:38:34,718 --> 00:38:36,962
I can barely pay the rent.

620
00:38:37,178 --> 00:38:42,302
I've never felt much
like a man in my life.

621
00:38:43,136 --> 00:38:45,390
My papa never taught me,

622
00:38:45,688 --> 00:38:49,392
but I want to be
a good dad to you.

623
00:38:49,647 --> 00:38:51,393
I'm gonna need your help.

624
00:38:51,685 --> 00:38:54,691
We gotta pull together
and make this work.

625
00:38:54,698 --> 00:38:57,902
- 'Cause it's just you and me.
- I'm sorry, Dad.

626
00:38:58,156 --> 00:38:59,942
I can try harder.

627
00:39:06,578 --> 00:39:08,492
Maybe this will help.

628
00:39:17,007 --> 00:39:18,590
Where'd you get...

629
00:39:19,096 --> 00:39:21,013
Where'd you get this from?

630
00:39:21,385 --> 00:39:24,051
You know how you and
Mom have a secret?

631
00:39:25,226 --> 00:39:28,263
Well, I have a secret too.

632
00:39:45,918 --> 00:39:47,243
Where are we?

633
00:39:47,876 --> 00:39:49,950
Your secret headquarters?

634
00:39:50,586 --> 00:39:52,292
You let us go now?

635
00:39:52,505 --> 00:39:54,082
That's up to the boss.

636
00:40:02,636 --> 00:40:04,051
Hiro, please.

637
00:40:04,227 --> 00:40:05,471
I don't want to meet the Boss.

638
00:40:05,685 --> 00:40:06,802
I want to go home.

639
00:40:07,058 --> 00:40:09,102
Tell them what
they want to hear.

640
00:40:09,688 --> 00:40:12,312
Do not be afraid, my friend.

641
00:40:12,528 --> 00:40:13,930
I shall never betray you.

642
00:40:14,065 --> 00:40:15,522
No matter what.

643
00:40:34,168 --> 00:40:36,003
Father?

644
00:40:40,465 --> 00:40:41,791
GULP!

645
00:40:52,687 --> 00:40:53,811
Hello?

646
00:40:54,686 --> 00:40:58,391
Hi, I'm looking for someone
related to Meredith Gordon.

647
00:40:58,697 --> 00:41:00,940
She died in an
explosion 14 years ago.

648
00:41:01,365 --> 00:41:05,692
I've been calling everyone in Kermit
with the last name of "Gordon."

649
00:41:05,698 --> 00:41:09,662
- Any chance that you're related to her?
- Who is this?

650
00:41:09,956 --> 00:41:12,410
My name's Claire Bennet,
I'm calling from Odessa.

651
00:41:12,708 --> 00:41:15,700
What... What is this about?

652
00:41:15,796 --> 00:41:18,291
And how do you know the
name "Meredith Gordon"?

653
00:41:18,545 --> 00:41:20,711
I think she was my mom.

654
00:41:21,007 --> 00:41:23,043
Is this some kind of joke?

655
00:41:23,345 --> 00:41:25,341
No, ma'am.

656
00:41:26,557 --> 00:41:29,763
Well, Meredith only
had one daughter, and

657
00:41:30,015 --> 00:41:32,091
she died in the fire.

658
00:41:33,228 --> 00:41:36,180
That's kind of what
I'm trying to say is...

659
00:41:36,356 --> 00:41:38,101
I didn't die.

660
00:41:38,397 --> 00:41:43,400
I think I'm her and I'm looking for any
information I can find about my mom.

661
00:41:44,576 --> 00:41:49,702
Well, then you made the right call.
This is her.

662
00:41:50,158 --> 00:41:52,071
Mom?

